{
  "texts": [
    "The model parameters are then iteratively optimized to minimize the cost function using optimization algorithms, i.e.",
    "Gradient Descent, AdaDelta, Adaptive Moment Estimation (Adam), RMSProp, Adagrad, Momentum, Nesterov Accelerated Gradient etc.",
    "Gradient Descent (GD) and its variants Batch GD and Stochastic Gradient Descent (SGD) are the most commonly employed optimization routines used in training.",
    "During the training process, patterns that characterize the underlying characteristics of the input-output relationship are extracted to inform the model prediction.",
    "In the fruit maturity context, ML models most commonly perform one of two tasks viz., classification or regression."
  ]
}